          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Build and cook",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the {{vegetable-oil}} in a pan over medium heat. Fry the {{onion}} for 4 minutes. Add the {{garlic}}, {{ginger-root}}, {{curry-powder}}, and {{turmeric}} and stir for 1 minute. Transfer to the slow cooker. Add the {{sweet-potato}}, {{butternut-squash}}, {{chickpeas-tinned}}, {{tinned-tomatoes}}, {{coconut-milk}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Cook on low for 5 to 6 hours, until the vegetables are tender. Stir in the {{garam-masala}} and {{spinach-frozen}} if using. Cover and wait 5 minutes for the spinach to wilt. Taste and adjust seasoning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "For next time, cut all vegetables into pieces at least 3 cm. Butternut squash especially needs to be kept large. It breaks down quickly",
              "cause": "Cut too small, or cooked longer than 6 hours",
              "symptom": "Vegetables have dissolved into the sauce"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Add 100 ml vegetable stock or water and stir to loosen. A squeeze of lime also cuts through the richness",
              "cause": "Full-fat coconut milk and starchy sweet potato have thickened the sauce significantly",
              "symptom": "Sauce very rich and thick"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Always fry the curry powder and turmeric in oil with the onion before adding to the slow cooker",
              "cause": "Spices added raw rather than bloomed first",
              "symptom": "Curry lacks depth"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Vegetable curry with coconut milk is a reliable plant-based slow-cooker dinner. The coconut milk provides body and richness without any dairy. It keeps for three days in the fridge and the flavour improves each day. Serve over basmati rice with flatbread and mango chutney.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
